**YOU:** “How do you bury people these days?”  

**PAOLO:** “No more church burials. Before, families walked them to holy ground. Now? A priest and two of us toss them in pits, quicklime on top, and that’s it. No prayers, no farewells.”  

[[Back|Gravedigger]]


:: Chapter1 {"position":"650,775","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/d94946_416c693b59614b3db07c57f2617d3ea7~mv2.png"
