''Just outside the ruins of a scorched alley near Via Castiglione''

Spada steps away from the gravedigger, his boots still dusted with lime. He follows the choking stench of vinegar and pitch until he sees a man in a waxed white coat hunched over a basin of smoking liquid. The figure coughs violently, then straightens with effort, revealing blistered skin beneath the edge of his soaked hood.

