**YOU:** “Aren’t you afraid?”  

**PAOLO:** “Fear’s wasted. We’ve lost twenty-three men in July and August alone—me breathing lime and rot all day. The air here tastes of decay and quicklime; that’s your sign that Meloncello’s not just a place name but ten thousand souls crying out from the dirt.”  

[[Back|Gravedigger]]


