''Grada sluice gate — fading light''

In the fading light, you spot a lone figure kneeling at the edge of the sluice—where the first mass grave overflowed weeks ago. Lime-dust coats his shoulders and beard.

**PAOLO (Gravedigger):**  
“Name’s Paolo, one of the gravediggers they pressed into service. Grada’s full as you see—couldn’t keep up with the bodies after the procession. They had to dig two more pits by the Reno River and down by the Savena torrent. Twenty-five per cart, they say. No coffins, no names… just lime to speed it up and hide the smell.”

**You can ask him：**  
[[What happened at Grada?|Grada]]  
[[How do you bury people these days?|Burial]]  
[[Who pays for burials?|Pay]]  
[[Aren’t you afraid?|Fear]]
