:: Helpless {"position":"900,1550","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/d94946_dd1310e2c91246dfa5921c222a1fb409~mv2.png"
     style="
       display: block;
       margin: 0 auto 1em;
       max-width: 70%;
       height: auto;
     " alt="Reveal">

**SPADA:**  
And the people?

**ZAZIO (bitter):**  
They call us ghouls. Throw stones at us. Some priests even say we're going against God's will, interfering with divine punishment. But we—  
*(pauses, wiping his eyes)*  
We do this because no one else will. This is our martyrdom. Of the sixty men, nine friars are dead. And I—  
*(he blinks rapidly)*  
The lime burned my eyes last week. I can't see properly anymore. Still, I lead them. I must.

**SPADA (softly):**  
You shouldn't be out here.

**ZAZIO:**  
If I stop now, they stop. And the city dies faster. We’ve cleaned over three thousand houses. We boil our gloves in pitch after every visit. Still, the stench sticks. It’s in our lungs. Our clothes. Our prayers.

[[Next|Duty]]


