:: Prologue_1 {"position":"650,200","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/d94946_e88c9cd2f5ab4c29925af62f8db3f94f~mv2.png"
     style="
       display: block;
       margin: 0 auto 1em;
       max-width: 70%;
       height: auto;
     " alt="Prologue">
''Council Chamber — Moments later''

ASSUNTERIA HEAD: (Tapping Modena on the map)
"Four hundred dead. Plague signs confirmed: buboes, black vomit. The Lansquenet troops brought it from Mantua’s siege. It moves faster than the Po in flood."

DR. AMBROSINI: (Leaning forward, urgent)
"Your Eminence, we must act! Close the gates. Isolate the sick. The canals reek of decay—miasma thickens in this unseasonable warmth. If it enters Bologna…"

SENATOR OTTAVIO: (Coolly interrupting)
"‘If’ is a beggar’s word, Doctor. We are a city of commerce. Close the gates, and what then? No grain from Ferrara. No cloth from Florence. The people will starve before the plague even touches them."
(He gestures to the Senate’s coat of arms—a lion clutching a sheaf of wheat.)

ASSUNTERIA HEAD: (Nodding)
"The Senator speaks wisely. Panic is deadlier than disease. Recall 1527? A ‘plague’ that killed a few hundred paupers in Borgo San Pietro—yet we called it a fever. Trade thrived. The city survived."

[[Next->Prologue_2]]

<audio src="https://static.wixstatic.com/mp3/d94946_755a947aba03441c9a32f2734ab63b18.mp3" autoplay></audio>



:: Prologue_2 {"position":"425,375","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/d94946_ffabc1f1139a46a38250e01bf4af91c9~mv2.png"
     style="
       display: block;
       margin: 0 auto 1em;
       max-width: 70%;
       height: auto;
     " alt="Prologue">

''Council Chamber — Moments later''

SPADA: (Eyes sharp as flint)
"You propose deception?"

OTTAVIO: (Spreading jeweled hands)
"Prudence, Eminence. Deny nothing publicly… but delay. No quarantine notices. No flight of merchants. Let the Assunteria handle ‘isolated incidents’ quietly."

AMBROSINI: (Appalled)
"People will die in the shadows! This is not 1527—this pestilence devours cities whole! Milan burns while its governors whisper lies!"

ASSUNTERIA HEAD: (Scoffing)
"Milan lacks our discipline. A few deaths in the slums? Wall off Borgo dell’Oro. Burn the corpses at night. The Senate will fund ‘sanitation improvements.’"

SPADA: (Staring into the fire)
Silence hangs thick. Rain drums like distant funeral march.
"And if it spreads beyond the slums?"

OTTAVIO: (Softly)
"Then God’s will be done. But if we cripple Bologna now? Famine will come. Riots will come. The Papal States will blame us. Better a silent plague than a starving mob."

AMBROSINI: (To Spada, pleading)
"Your Eminence—!"


