:: Situation {"position":"900,1425","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/d94946_c15caa6dab4a45fbb674c2006663e796~mv2.png"
     style="
       display: block;
       margin: 0 auto 1em;
       max-width: 70%;
       height: auto;
     " alt="Reveal">

**SPADA (grimacing):**  
God have mercy. And the work?

**ZAZIO:**  
Relentless. First we mark the dead houses with the red cross. Some streets are sealed off entirely. We scrape walls down to brick, douse them with lime-water. Beds, clothes—burnt in the open. If it smells foul, we torch it. Even the letters are washed in zinc before a courier touches them.

**SPADA:**  
And the cost?

**ZAZIO (dry laugh):**  
Ask the Senate. They say we’re draining the treasury—200 lire a day. They'd rather fund grain subsidies than stop the plague. But you should see the nobles—paying off officials to keep their doors unmarked while servants rot inside.

[[Next|Helpless]]

<audio src="https://static.wixstatic.com/mp3/d94946_a1a701de882f4423985d6078bb9f02be.mp3" autoplay></audio>



