''November, 1629 — Palazzo Pubblico, Bologna''

Rain lashes against leaded windows, casting watery shadows across the Council Chamber. A fire gutters in the hearth, failing to dispel the damp chill seeping from marble floors. Maps of Northern Italy lie strewn across an oak table, marked with ominous red crosses near Modena and Mantua. The air smells of ink, wet wool, and fear.

