:: The End {"position":"900,1800","size":"100,100"}
(hook: "overlay")[]

<img src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/d94946_5a4fca0f5acd49feb91695b3d49d850d~mv2.png"
     style="
       display: block;
       margin: 0 auto 1em;
       max-width: 70%;
       height: auto;
     " alt="Reveal">

Spada stands atop the Asinelli Tower at dawn. Below, Bologna stirs: market carts return, children chase rats, lime-scarred purgatori shuffle home. He opens a ledger—page after page of the dead—then tears it out, letting wind scatter the names over the rooftops.

**SPADA:**  
"We built lazarettos to contain the sick, and walls to contain the truth. But the dead needed no containment. They were Bologna’s silent witnesses. Let them speak now."

